WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:50.300 --> 00:01:54.140
Those three think they can
mock me? Screw that!

3
00:01:54.140 --> 00:01:57.970
I'm considering this
a formal declaration of war.

4
00:01:58.720 --> 00:02:01.180
Perfect timing, Mohji!

5
00:02:01.560 --> 00:02:06.270
Mohji "the Beast Tamer"
First Mate of the Buggy Pirates

6
00:02:02.810 --> 00:02:06.270
Mind if I go after Roronoa Zoro?

7
00:02:06.810 --> 00:02:07.820
Be my guest.

8
00:02:19.870 --> 00:02:25.500
Treasure

9
00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:27.880
What's with that dog?

10
00:02:28.800 --> 00:02:30.300
A dog!

11
00:02:36.300 --> 00:02:39.260
Hey, Zoro! It's not moving at all!

12
00:02:39.260 --> 00:02:42.180
Hell if I care! It can
do whatever it wants!

13
00:02:42.890 --> 00:02:44.390
Think it's dead?

14
00:02:50.320 --> 00:02:53.740
Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow! Yee-ow!

15
00:02:53.740 --> 00:02:58.070
Ow, ow, ow! What's the big deal,
you stupid dog?!

16
00:02:58.070 --> 00:03:01.330
Would you stop messing around
at a time like this?!

17
00:03:04.160 --> 00:03:05.580
Stupid dog...

18
00:03:05.580 --> 00:03:07.290
Not enough blood...

19
00:03:11.250 --> 00:03:12.960
Hey, Navigator!

20
00:03:13.720 --> 00:03:17.390
I guess you can have this
since you saved me!

21
00:03:18.890 --> 00:03:20.970
Oh! The key to the cage!

22
00:03:20.970 --> 00:03:23.850
You went and got it for me?!

23
00:03:23.850 --> 00:03:25.850
Now we're even.

24
00:03:27.350 --> 00:03:28.400
I'm saved!

25
00:03:39.870 --> 00:03:42.450
You stupid, stupid dog! Stupid dog!

26
00:03:42.450 --> 00:03:45.710
That's not food!
Gimme back that key!

27
00:03:45.710 --> 00:03:49.130
You stupid, stupid,
stupid, stupid dog!

28
00:03:49.130 --> 00:03:51.210
Gimme! Gimme! Gimme!

29
00:03:51.210 --> 00:03:52.670
Stop that!

30
00:03:53.670 --> 00:03:56.630
Quit bullying Chouchou,
you delinquents!

31
00:03:57.760 --> 00:03:58.380
Chouchou?

32
00:03:58.760 --> 00:04:00.470
Who are you, old-timer?

33
00:04:00.470 --> 00:04:03.220
I'm this town's mayor!

34
00:04:00.510 --> 00:04:06.390
Boodle
Harbor Village Mayor

35
00:04:03.220 --> 00:04:05.930
Who are you?!

36
00:04:05.930 --> 00:04:06.390
Huh?

37
00:04:13.730 --> 00:04:14.980
How's Zoro?!

38
00:04:14.980 --> 00:04:17.450
He needs to see a doctor,

39
00:04:17.450 --> 00:04:20.780
but he said he'd sleep it off
and went to bed.

40
00:04:23.830 --> 00:04:26.330
So this dog's name is Chouchou?

41
00:04:26.950 --> 00:04:29.960
What's he just sitting here for?

42
00:04:30.290 --> 00:04:31.830
He's guarding the shop.

43
00:04:32.340 --> 00:04:36.630
Oh! This is... a pet food shop?

44
00:04:36.630 --> 00:04:42.260
Yes. A good friend of mine
owned this shop.

45
00:04:46.680 --> 00:04:47.560
There you go.

46
00:04:50.440 --> 00:04:55.020
I'm just here to feed
his dog in his place.

47
00:04:55.940 --> 00:04:56.820
"In his place"?

48
00:04:56.820 --> 00:04:57.900
Yes.

49
00:04:57.900 --> 00:05:03.370
He passed away. An illness
took him three months ago.

50
00:05:03.370 --> 00:05:07.750
You mean to tell us he's been waiting
here for his master all this time?

51
00:05:10.500 --> 00:05:12.170
That's the general consensus...

52
00:05:17.960 --> 00:05:20.590
but I don't think that's the case.

53
00:05:21.550 --> 00:05:23.930
Chouchou is a smart dog.

54
00:05:23.930 --> 00:05:27.720
He's probably long since realized
that his master has passed on.

55
00:05:32.310 --> 00:05:34.810
Then why is he guarding the shop?

56
00:05:34.810 --> 00:05:38.820
I believe it's because Chouchou
regards this shop as his treasure.

57
00:05:39.150 --> 00:05:45.120
I think he continues to protect it
in memory of his loving master.

58
00:05:45.490 --> 00:05:49.660
I've tried to get him somewhere
safer on many occasions,

59
00:05:49.660 --> 00:05:52.080
but he won't budge from this spot.

60
00:06:07.720 --> 00:06:09.220
Huh? What are those roars?!

61
00:06:09.220 --> 00:06:12.230
It's him! Mohji the Beast Tamer!

62
00:06:13.440 --> 00:06:15.400
What do you mean "Beast Tamer"?!

63
00:06:15.400 --> 00:06:17.270
W-Wait! Hold on!

64
00:06:18.020 --> 00:06:20.030
C'mon, something's coming.

65
00:06:20.030 --> 00:06:21.860
Gimme back the key.

66
00:06:26.660 --> 00:06:29.290
Oh, I see your friends
have deserted you.

67
00:06:29.290 --> 00:06:31.080
And you had only just escaped…

68
00:06:31.750 --> 00:06:32.870
Who are you?

69
00:06:33.710 --> 00:06:37.290
I am Mohji the Beast Tamer,
a member of the Buggy Pirates.

70
00:06:37.840 --> 00:06:40.840
That sure is a weird
animal suit you got on!

71
00:06:41.210 --> 00:06:43.930
How rude! This is my hair!

72
00:06:44.180 --> 00:06:45.760
That's even weirder!

73
00:06:45.760 --> 00:06:50.060
Do you think you're safe
just because you're in that cage?

74
00:06:50.060 --> 00:06:51.850
You must not know who I am!

75
00:06:51.850 --> 00:06:57.270
There is no animal in this world that
Mohji the Beast Tamer cannot tame!

76
00:06:58.190 --> 00:06:58.900
Shake!

77
00:07:00.190 --> 00:07:02.490
Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!

78
00:07:02.490 --> 00:07:02.530
Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!

79
00:07:02.530 --> 00:07:02.570
Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!

80
00:07:02.570 --> 00:07:02.610
Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!

81
00:07:02.610 --> 00:07:02.650
Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!

82
00:07:02.650 --> 00:07:02.690
Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!

83
00:07:02.690 --> 00:07:02.740
Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!

84
00:07:02.740 --> 00:07:02.780
Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!

85
00:07:02.780 --> 00:07:02.820
Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!

86
00:07:02.820 --> 00:07:02.860
Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!

87
00:07:04.070 --> 00:07:06.240
You're just some nameless thief.

88
00:07:06.240 --> 00:07:09.950
I couldn't care less if you live or die.
Tell me where Roronoa Zoro is!

89
00:07:10.370 --> 00:07:11.450
No!

90
00:07:11.990 --> 00:07:13.410
Sic him, Richie!

91
00:07:16.170 --> 00:07:19.000
Nice! The cage is open!

92
00:07:24.880 --> 00:07:26.300
Instant death.

93
00:07:26.840 --> 00:07:28.300
Good boy, Richie.

94
00:07:28.300 --> 00:07:32.930
Now, let's find Zoro. Defeating him
will bolster my reputation.

95
00:07:32.930 --> 00:07:34.810
Hm? What is it?

96
00:07:34.810 --> 00:07:36.520
Ah, a pet food store.

97
00:07:36.520 --> 00:07:38.440
Fine, but eat quickly!

98
00:07:40.980 --> 00:07:42.270
What the...?

99
00:07:42.270 --> 00:07:47.150
Is this mutt really trying to keep us
out of this pathetic little shop?

100
00:07:51.530 --> 00:07:53.950
Phew, what a shock!

101
00:07:53.950 --> 00:07:55.960
But at least I'm out of that cage.

102
00:07:58.250 --> 00:07:59.250
Alright!

103
00:07:59.250 --> 00:08:03.710
Now I can kick some butt and get
that thief Nami to be our navigator!

104
00:08:04.920 --> 00:08:06.470
How did you survive that?!

105
00:08:06.470 --> 00:08:06.510
How did you survive that?!

106
00:08:06.510 --> 00:08:06.550
How did you survive that?!

107
00:08:06.550 --> 00:08:06.590
How did you survive that?!

108
00:08:06.590 --> 00:08:06.630
You're alive!

109
00:08:06.630 --> 00:08:06.670
You're alive!

110
00:08:06.670 --> 00:08:06.720
You're alive!

111
00:08:06.720 --> 00:08:06.760
You're alive!

112
00:08:06.760 --> 00:08:06.800
You're alive!

113
00:08:06.800 --> 00:08:06.840
You're alive!

114
00:08:06.840 --> 00:08:06.880
You're alive!

115
00:08:06.880 --> 00:08:06.920
You're alive!

116
00:08:06.920 --> 00:08:07.630
You're alive!

117
00:08:07.630 --> 00:08:09.430
Something wrong with that?

118
00:08:09.430 --> 00:08:13.970
People don't normally crash through
buildings and walk away from it!

119
00:08:13.970 --> 00:08:15.470
They don't?

120
00:08:15.470 --> 00:08:18.890
Why did you come to
this town in the first place?

121
00:08:18.890 --> 00:08:20.810
Why get mixed up with those pirates?

122
00:08:20.810 --> 00:08:22.940
I've just now decided on our goal.

123
00:08:22.940 --> 00:08:25.780
To get a map to the Grand Line
and find a navigator!

124
00:08:28.860 --> 00:08:32.580
That guy in the animal costume was
looking for Zoro! I gotta find him!

125
00:08:44.250 --> 00:08:49.720
Chouchou, this shop
belongs to the two of us!

126
00:08:53.890 --> 00:08:56.770
This bag is too big
for you, Chouchou!

127
00:09:12.620 --> 00:09:15.030
You don't want
to get hurt, Chouchou!

128
00:09:15.030 --> 00:09:16.540
Just leave it to me!

129
00:09:19.750 --> 00:09:22.750
Bad Chouchou! I told you
not to eat the merchandise!

130
00:09:23.380 --> 00:09:24.790
Now let's chow down!

131
00:09:34.970 --> 00:09:38.140
Oh? You've still got
some fight left in you...

132
00:09:40.310 --> 00:09:43.350
Chouchou, I'm getting
up there in years now.

133
00:09:43.350 --> 00:09:45.690
I gotta check in to the hospital.

134
00:09:45.690 --> 00:09:48.900
But... I'm going to get better!

135
00:09:48.900 --> 00:09:51.820
Guard the shop well
until I come back!

136
00:09:52.200 --> 00:09:54.780
Hold down the fort!

137
00:10:23.060 --> 00:10:25.440
That tickles, Chouchou!

138
00:10:31.360 --> 00:10:34.910
I believe it's because Chouchou
regards this shop as his treasure.

139
00:10:35.490 --> 00:10:41.080
I think he continues to protect it
in memory of his loving master.

140
00:11:04.940 --> 00:11:08.020
Damn it! That dog even bit me!

141
00:11:15.820 --> 00:11:18.780
Wait! I just killed you!

142
00:11:21.080 --> 00:11:23.410
It'll take more than that to kill me!

143
00:11:24.160 --> 00:11:27.420
Crush his head for sure this time!

144
00:11:30.670 --> 00:11:32.840
I won't lose to some lion!

145
00:11:33.760 --> 00:11:35.340
Gum-Gum...

146
00:11:39.090 --> 00:11:41.100
Hammer!

147
00:11:45.230 --> 00:11:47.230
Richie!

148
00:11:49.900 --> 00:11:52.440
Just what the hell are you?!

149
00:11:53.610 --> 00:11:57.150
I ate the Gum-Gum Fruit!

150
00:11:57.740 --> 00:12:03.120
Wait, you have devil fruit powers
just like Captain Buggy?!

151
00:12:07.160 --> 00:12:10.960
I-I get the picture!
Please accept my humble apology!

152
00:12:12.290 --> 00:12:14.590
It's too late for apologies...

153
00:12:14.590 --> 00:12:16.970
That dog's treasure
is gone forever.

154
00:12:20.010 --> 00:12:21.350
That's why...

155
00:12:21.350 --> 00:12:23.720
I'm gonna kick your ass!

156
00:12:44.790 --> 00:12:49.160
Pirates are all the same,
every last one!

157
00:12:50.080 --> 00:12:53.130
They take what people hold dear
without a second thought!

158
00:12:53.790 --> 00:12:55.840
So you survived, pirate!

159
00:12:56.210 --> 00:13:00.840
I figured the lion would've
eaten you for sure!

160
00:13:00.840 --> 00:13:03.680
As a pirate, you'll end up
doing the same thing!

161
00:13:04.510 --> 00:13:07.310
You'll gather a crew
and raid town after town!

162
00:13:07.310 --> 00:13:09.640
I should kill you before
you get the chance!

163
00:13:09.640 --> 00:13:12.060
Hey! Stop it, young lady!

164
00:13:12.060 --> 00:13:13.730
As if you could ever kill me.

165
00:13:13.730 --> 00:13:15.190
Let's test that theory!

166
00:13:15.190 --> 00:13:17.650
I said stop! What's with you people?!

167
00:13:31.620 --> 00:13:33.630
This is all I was able to get back.

168
00:13:33.630 --> 00:13:36.090
That bastard went and ate the rest!

169
00:13:36.920 --> 00:13:41.260
He... fought with that lion.

170
00:13:41.260 --> 00:13:42.720
All for that dog's sake.

171
00:13:46.470 --> 00:13:48.470
You fought good!

172
00:13:48.470 --> 00:13:50.980
I didn't see you in action,
but I can tell!

173
00:14:10.660 --> 00:14:11.660
Yeah!

174
00:14:12.250 --> 00:14:13.580
Good luck to you, too!

175
00:14:28.470 --> 00:14:30.810
You were beaten?!

176
00:14:31.350 --> 00:14:34.600
I-I'm very sorry, Captain Buggy!

177
00:14:35.270 --> 00:14:38.610
Mohji! I can't believe
you'd lose to Zoro!

178
00:14:39.020 --> 00:14:41.400
No, it wasn't Zoro!
It was Straw Hat!

179
00:14:41.860 --> 00:14:45.530
What?! You got beat by
the kid in the straw hat?!

180
00:14:45.530 --> 00:14:47.370
He ate the... Gum...

181
00:14:47.370 --> 00:14:49.990
Now I'm pissed!

182
00:14:49.990 --> 00:14:52.250
Ready all the Special Buggy Balls!

183
00:14:52.250 --> 00:14:55.370
I'm gonna blow this
entire town to smithereens!

184
00:14:57.170 --> 00:14:58.170
Sorry for earlier!

185
00:14:58.840 --> 00:14:59.920
Huh?

186
00:14:59.920 --> 00:15:01.630
I didn't mean to yell at you...

187
00:15:02.300 --> 00:15:05.380
It's okay! You've been through a lot!

188
00:15:06.930 --> 00:15:09.180
I don't need the details, though.

189
00:15:09.560 --> 00:15:11.350
I'm so pathetic!

190
00:15:11.350 --> 00:15:14.520
If Chouchou and this youngster
won't back down,

191
00:15:14.520 --> 00:15:19.610
then why am I, as mayor, content
to watch the town get destroyed?!

192
00:15:19.980 --> 00:15:21.610
Calm down, Mayor!

193
00:15:21.610 --> 00:15:25.740
Forty years ago, this place
was nothing but barren land.

194
00:15:25.740 --> 00:15:29.620
We all worked together
to clear and till the land,

195
00:15:29.620 --> 00:15:32.950
open stores, and build our town.

196
00:15:32.950 --> 00:15:37.250
This town is a treasure
to me and all its citizens!

197
00:15:37.250 --> 00:15:41.000
I won't let them have their
way with it any longer!

198
00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:45.010
Fire a Special Buggy Ball!
Blow the town away!

199
00:15:56.310 --> 00:15:58.650
Even my own house...

200
00:16:00.150 --> 00:16:01.610
Zoro's sleeping in there!

201
00:16:01.610 --> 00:16:04.940
That young man must be dead...

202
00:16:05.860 --> 00:16:07.950
Hey! Zoro! Are you alive?!

203
00:16:08.410 --> 00:16:10.990
That's a hell of a way
to wake a guy up.

204
00:16:14.410 --> 00:16:17.790
Not enough sleep...

205
00:16:18.580 --> 00:16:20.580
And just how did you survive?!

206
00:16:20.580 --> 00:16:22.420
Thank goodness! You're alive!

207
00:16:22.840 --> 00:16:26.260
No more sitting idly by
while they run wild here...

208
00:16:26.720 --> 00:16:28.130
I've had it up to here!

209
00:16:28.130 --> 00:16:33.640
These scumbags have zero right
to trample on these forty years!

210
00:16:35.600 --> 00:16:39.020
I am this town's mayor!

211
00:16:40.270 --> 00:16:43.940
I will protect this town!

212
00:16:44.940 --> 00:16:46.900
Stop! Stop, Mayor!

213
00:16:46.900 --> 00:16:50.280
No...! There are some fights
a man can't run away from!

214
00:16:50.280 --> 00:16:51.950
Isn't that right, kiddo?!

215
00:16:51.950 --> 00:16:53.200
That's right, old guy!

216
00:16:53.990 --> 00:16:55.330
Don't encourage him!

217
00:16:55.330 --> 00:16:58.080
What's he gonna change
by facing them?! It's reckless!

218
00:16:58.620 --> 00:17:00.040
It's absolutely reckless!

219
00:17:03.170 --> 00:17:07.460
I'm coming for you, Buggy the Clown!

220
00:17:08.260 --> 00:17:10.180
The mayor was crying...

221
00:17:10.180 --> 00:17:12.640
He was? Not that I could see.

222
00:17:12.640 --> 00:17:15.010
Looks like the party's
getting more exciting!

223
00:17:16.010 --> 00:17:17.270
You said it!

224
00:17:18.140 --> 00:17:19.940
This is no time to be laughing!

225
00:17:20.980 --> 00:17:21.980
It's okay!

226
00:17:21.980 --> 00:17:23.940
I like that old guy!

227
00:17:23.940 --> 00:17:25.400
I'd never let him die!

228
00:17:25.820 --> 00:17:27.570
In that case...

229
00:17:28.320 --> 00:17:30.240
You're going too?!
But you're wounded!

230
00:17:30.820 --> 00:17:36.030
The injury to my name is much worse
than the injury to my gut!

231
00:17:36.410 --> 00:17:38.950
We're headed for the Grand Line.

232
00:17:39.450 --> 00:17:42.370
So we're gonna swipe
that map back from them!

233
00:17:44.130 --> 00:17:46.460
Join our crew, Nami!

234
00:17:47.500 --> 00:17:50.170
I won't become a pirate.

235
00:17:53.010 --> 00:17:56.560
But how about this? We team up
to achieve a common goal!

236
00:17:57.100 --> 00:17:59.560
The second shot is ready, sir!

237
00:17:59.560 --> 00:18:01.020
Alright! Fire!

238
00:18:01.020 --> 00:18:04.520
Get out here, Buggy the Clown!

239
00:18:07.480 --> 00:18:10.030
I am Mayor Boodle!

240
00:18:10.030 --> 00:18:13.990
This town is our treasure, so I'm
going to protect it by taking you out!

241
00:18:14.320 --> 00:18:16.240
What are you, stupid?!

242
00:18:16.240 --> 00:18:18.990
Treasure is gold, silver, and jewels!

243
00:18:18.990 --> 00:18:20.410
This town, a treasure?!

244
00:18:20.410 --> 00:18:21.960
Cut the crap!

245
00:18:21.960 --> 00:18:24.750
You'd never understand how I feel–

246
00:18:26.210 --> 00:18:32.630
Soon, I'll conquer the Grand Line and
flashily obtain all of the world's riches!

247
00:18:32.630 --> 00:18:34.760
It'll all belong to me!

248
00:18:34.760 --> 00:18:37.640
No one else in this world
needs treasure but me!

249
00:18:37.640 --> 00:18:42.100
Since you love this town so much,
shall I level it along with you?

250
00:18:42.850 --> 00:18:45.770
Quit blowing hot air and fight me!

251
00:18:46.230 --> 00:18:47.690
Don't get cocky now!

252
00:18:48.110 --> 00:18:53.650
The only way you'll destroy
this town is over my dead body!

253
00:18:53.650 --> 00:18:54.990
Fire!

254
00:18:57.370 --> 00:18:59.030
The straw hat guy!

255
00:19:03.870 --> 00:19:07.540
I'm here to kick your ass,
just like I promised!

256
00:19:16.430 --> 00:19:20.810
How dare you just waltz back here...

257
00:19:20.810 --> 00:19:23.810
to Captain Buggy!

258
00:19:23.810 --> 00:19:28.400
Listen! All I want is
the map and the treasure!

259
00:19:28.400 --> 00:19:29.820
Yeah, we know.

260
00:19:31.020 --> 00:19:33.900
Youngsters... Why'd you come here?!

261
00:19:33.900 --> 00:19:37.280
This isn't your business, so butt out!

262
00:19:38.070 --> 00:19:39.780
This is my fight!

263
00:19:39.780 --> 00:19:43.500
I will protect my town!

264
00:19:46.000 --> 00:19:47.330
Now stop meddling!

265
00:19:55.800 --> 00:19:57.550
What the hell?!

266
00:19:58.090 --> 00:20:00.510
Why did you attack the mayor?!

267
00:20:01.510 --> 00:20:02.430
He was in the way!

268
00:20:03.520 --> 00:20:05.180
Good thinking.

269
00:20:05.180 --> 00:20:07.640
No doubt this geezer
was prepared to die.

270
00:20:08.600 --> 00:20:09.940
This is for the best.

271
00:20:09.940 --> 00:20:11.650
But this is going overboard!

272
00:20:11.650 --> 00:20:14.650
There were plenty of other ways
you could've done it!

273
00:20:20.950 --> 00:20:24.830
Hey, Big Nose!

274
00:20:25.790 --> 00:20:28.120
That's the one thing
you shouldn't say!

275
00:20:28.120 --> 00:20:31.790
You're dead meat,
you flashy mongrel!

276
00:20:31.790 --> 00:20:34.460
How dare you...?

277
00:20:34.460 --> 00:20:36.670
Flashily fire the Buggy Ball!

278
00:20:37.760 --> 00:20:40.300
Why'd you say that, you idiot?!

279
00:20:40.300 --> 00:20:41.930
Hey, Luffy! Run!

280
00:20:41.930 --> 00:20:42.970
That...

281
00:20:42.970 --> 00:20:44.350
Time to blow up!

282
00:20:44.850 --> 00:20:46.850
...won't work on me!

283
00:20:48.190 --> 00:20:49.730
Gum-Gum...

284
00:20:51.100 --> 00:20:52.770
Balloon!

285
00:20:55.190 --> 00:20:56.570
What is that guy?!

286
00:20:56.570 --> 00:20:58.030
But the Buggy Ball will...

287
00:21:00.990 --> 00:21:02.570
He bounced it back!

288
00:21:02.870 --> 00:21:04.530
Give us a heads up first, will you?!

289
00:21:12.920 --> 00:21:14.420
Alright! Took some out!

290
00:21:14.420 --> 00:21:16.630
Seriously, what are you?!

291
00:21:16.630 --> 00:21:18.380
You had me there for a sec.

292
00:21:26.720 --> 00:21:30.190
Ever since fighting that lion,
I knew you weren't quite normal!

293
00:21:30.480 --> 00:21:33.860
No human can do that!
Explain yourself!

294
00:21:33.860 --> 00:21:36.940
What was that balloon-inflating
thing you just did?!

295
00:21:37.320 --> 00:21:39.110
That's Gum-Gum Balloon!

296
00:21:39.110 --> 00:21:41.150
And how did you do that?!

297
00:21:41.700 --> 00:21:43.320
What are you, a monster?!

298
00:21:45.240 --> 00:21:48.830
How dare you flashily
try to do me in...

299
00:21:54.210 --> 00:21:56.630
He used his henchmen as shields!

300
00:22:00.420 --> 00:22:04.140
I couldn't eat another bite... H-Huh?

301
00:22:05.300 --> 00:22:07.350
What happened here?!

302
00:22:09.310 --> 00:22:11.020
You!

303
00:22:11.600 --> 00:22:12.140
Hey!

304
00:22:12.810 --> 00:22:14.810
The straw hat guy!

305
00:22:14.810 --> 00:22:17.190
C-C-Captain Buggy! Be careful!

306
00:22:17.190 --> 00:22:19.280
He has devil fruit powers too!

307
00:22:19.280 --> 00:22:21.150
He's a rubber man!

308
00:22:21.150 --> 00:22:22.150
What?!

309
00:22:22.490 --> 00:22:23.610
A rubber man?!

310
00:22:23.610 --> 00:22:25.950
Yeah, see?

311
00:22:26.410 --> 00:22:28.160
A devil fruit, huh...?

312
00:22:28.160 --> 00:22:31.660
That explains how he
bounced back the Buggy Ball.

313
00:22:34.830 --> 00:22:40.550
Cabaji "the Acrobat"
First Officer of the Buggy Pirates

314
00:22:35.330 --> 00:22:38.340
Our pirate crew has never been so insulted...

315
00:22:39.590 --> 00:22:40.550
Captain.

316
00:22:40.550 --> 00:22:45.510
Oh, Cabaji! I'm so angry
I'm seeing red.

317
00:22:45.510 --> 00:22:48.970
Cabaji! What the hell
did you do to Richie?!

318
00:22:48.970 --> 00:22:50.560
This cat?

319
00:22:50.560 --> 00:22:53.690
I used it to shield me
so I wouldn't get my clothes dirty.

320
00:22:55.520 --> 00:22:56.480
Richie!

321
00:22:58.650 --> 00:23:01.940
Hey, Richie! Say something!
Are you all right?!

322
00:23:05.860 --> 00:23:07.370
Richie!

323
00:23:07.370 --> 00:23:09.330
Dammit, you bastard!

324
00:23:12.370 --> 00:23:13.500
Out of the way!

325
00:23:13.870 --> 00:23:16.210
No, you get outta my way!

326
00:23:27.430 --> 00:23:34.890
I, First Officer Cabaji the Acrobat,
will manifest Captain Buggy's displeasure!

327
00:23:36.690 --> 00:23:39.270
I'll cross swords with you.

328
00:23:39.860 --> 00:23:42.570
Quite the honor, Roronoa Zoro.

329
00:23:43.440 --> 00:23:46.740
As a swordsman myself, it will
be my pleasure to cut you down.

330
00:23:49.490 --> 00:23:51.700
Hey, Zoro! You should really rest!

331
00:23:51.700 --> 00:23:52.740
I'll handle this!

332
00:23:52.740 --> 00:23:54.960
Stay out of this!

333
00:23:54.960 --> 00:23:58.500
That's the stab wound
the captain gave him. What a fool.

334
00:23:59.080 --> 00:24:00.960
Acrobatics: Dire Fire!

335
00:24:10.850 --> 00:24:12.100
Something wrong?

336
00:24:12.100 --> 00:24:14.600
I'm sure I didn't kick you that hard.

337
00:24:15.020 --> 00:24:17.730
He attacked his injury! He fights dirty!

338
00:24:19.810 --> 00:24:22.940
Acrobatics: Steamy Hot Spring
Murder Mystery!

339
00:24:26.320 --> 00:24:27.900
Acrobatics, my ass!

340
00:24:27.900 --> 00:24:29.860
That's just kicking up dust!

341
00:24:35.870 --> 00:24:36.960
He did it again!

342
00:24:38.580 --> 00:24:42.920
What's wrong? A grown man
wailing is disgraceful!

343
00:24:43.500 --> 00:24:46.510
Well? Now do you see
how foolish it was...

344
00:24:46.510 --> 00:24:50.890
to make an enemy
of the Buggy Pirates?

345
00:24:51.390 --> 00:24:54.890
As hurt as he is,
it's a miracle he's still alive!

346
00:24:55.520 --> 00:24:58.890
Why are you just standing there?!
He's gonna get killed!

347
00:25:06.480 --> 00:25:07.940
Roronoa Zoro...

348
00:25:08.740 --> 00:25:09.570
You're finished!

349
00:25:10.780 --> 00:25:12.740
Annoying bastard!

350
00:25:14.740 --> 00:25:17.040
Is poking my wound...

351
00:25:17.040 --> 00:25:19.330
that much fun?!

352
00:25:22.250 --> 00:25:23.130
Ow!

353
00:25:28.130 --> 00:25:30.340
Wh-Why didn't you dodge that?!

354
00:25:31.220 --> 00:25:34.720
Is that enough
of a handicap for you?

355
00:25:35.850 --> 00:25:40.640
Now I'll show you...
just how outclassed you are!

356
00:25:41.640 --> 00:25:42.730
Whoa!

357
00:25:42.730 --> 00:25:43.770
So cool!

358
00:25:45.020 --> 00:25:47.780
So this is Roronoa Zoro, huh?

359
00:25:47.780 --> 00:25:49.070
You think you can mock me...

360
00:25:49.490 --> 00:25:52.360
I won't stop until
my swords rise to the top.

361
00:25:52.910 --> 00:25:58.080
I can't lose even once to anyone
who's considered a swordsman!

362
00:25:58.080 --> 00:25:59.040
I see...

363
00:26:00.120 --> 00:26:02.750
A strong resolve keeps you going.

364
00:26:03.580 --> 00:26:05.500
But never fear.

365
00:26:06.040 --> 00:26:09.550
Wounds as bad as yours will
make an excellent excuse...

366
00:26:10.010 --> 00:26:12.510
to explain why you lost to me!

367
00:26:12.510 --> 00:26:14.510
To hell with that...

368
00:26:15.140 --> 00:26:19.810
If I lose to someone like you
when I'm barely even injured...

369
00:26:19.810 --> 00:26:22.770
then my future isn't looking too bright!

370
00:26:24.310 --> 00:26:26.190
Why, you...!

371
00:26:26.190 --> 00:26:28.230
You got this, Zoro!

372
00:26:29.780 --> 00:26:31.530
This is too much for me.

373
00:26:31.530 --> 00:26:36.030
You pirates go and get
yourselves killed for all I care.

374
00:26:36.030 --> 00:26:40.870
Besides, I have no stake
in whether you win or lose.

375
00:26:40.870 --> 00:26:44.670
I'm gonna use this chance to swipe
their treasure and get outta here!

376
00:26:44.670 --> 00:26:45.670
Wha...?

377
00:26:46.420 --> 00:26:48.920
Let's team up again
if we ever get the chance!

378
00:26:49.340 --> 00:26:51.630
See ya! Good luck with the fight!

379
00:26:51.630 --> 00:26:53.380
Yeah! Thanks!

380
00:26:53.840 --> 00:26:56.640
Taste my ultimate acrobatic move!

381
00:27:00.430 --> 00:27:03.690
Acrobatics: 100 Whirling
Kamikaze Dervishes!

382
00:27:08.860 --> 00:27:09.820
Acrobatics...

383
00:27:10.360 --> 00:27:12.240
Alpine Ascent!

384
00:27:13.240 --> 00:27:16.360
Acrobatics:
Midsummer Fireworks!

385
00:27:16.360 --> 00:27:18.370
Whoa, he's flying!

386
00:27:18.370 --> 00:27:20.700
Sting of the Unicycle!

387
00:27:21.660 --> 00:27:24.830
Ground-Hugging
Chop-Chop Cannon!

388
00:27:27.250 --> 00:27:29.670
Cabaji! I'll hold Zoro down!

389
00:27:29.670 --> 00:27:30.960
You finish him off!

390
00:27:30.960 --> 00:27:32.420
As you wish!

391
00:27:33.630 --> 00:27:36.260
You bastards!

392
00:27:42.020 --> 00:27:42.850
Luffy!

393
00:27:43.850 --> 00:27:45.520
C-Curse you!

394
00:27:46.310 --> 00:27:48.150
Zoro's fight...

395
00:27:48.810 --> 00:27:50.150
is off limits.

396
00:27:54.150 --> 00:27:58.660
I can defeat you easily enough
without my captain's help!

397
00:27:58.660 --> 00:28:00.160
Enough...

398
00:28:00.160 --> 00:28:01.410
I'm tired...

399
00:28:04.120 --> 00:28:06.250
Finally given up, have you?

400
00:28:07.420 --> 00:28:11.500
Though I must say, I'm impressed
you could fight with such injuries.

401
00:28:12.380 --> 00:28:18.550
I-I meant I'm tired...
of your third-rate acrobatics!

402
00:28:20.140 --> 00:28:23.890
Then I'll finish you off... with my...

403
00:28:25.020 --> 00:28:27.310
real swordsmanship!

404
00:28:29.100 --> 00:28:30.310
Die!

405
00:28:32.440 --> 00:28:33.230
Oni...

406
00:28:34.030 --> 00:28:34.780
Giri!

407
00:28:39.280 --> 00:28:40.320
Cabaji!

408
00:28:42.620 --> 00:28:45.290
We, the Buggy Pirates...

409
00:28:45.290 --> 00:28:47.710
beaten by mere thieves!

410
00:28:51.500 --> 00:28:53.340
"Thieves"? Nah...

411
00:28:56.840 --> 00:28:58.880
We're pirates!

412
00:29:00.390 --> 00:29:02.970
Luffy! I'm gonna sleep now!

413
00:29:02.970 --> 00:29:04.140
Right!

414
00:29:04.140 --> 00:29:05.850
I'll handle the rest!

415
00:29:10.730 --> 00:29:13.650
You guys are pirates?!

416
00:29:13.650 --> 00:29:16.690
Yeah! We're headed
for the Grand Line!

417
00:29:17.570 --> 00:29:23.030
Half-baked nobodies like you can't
handle that kind of voyage, dimwit!

418
00:29:23.030 --> 00:29:27.160
What are you gonna do
in the Grand Line, anyway?!

419
00:29:27.160 --> 00:29:29.410
Go on a sightseeing trip
or something?

420
00:29:33.790 --> 00:29:35.130
Become King of the Pirates!

421
00:29:36.710 --> 00:29:38.840
Get real, you flashy fool!

422
00:29:38.840 --> 00:29:42.800
If you're King of the Pirates,
then I may as well be a god!

423
00:29:42.800 --> 00:29:46.810
I'll be King of the Pirates
and obtain all the world's treasures!

424
00:29:46.810 --> 00:29:48.930
Dream on!

425
00:29:48.930 --> 00:29:50.480
You're annoying.

426
00:29:51.100 --> 00:29:53.230
Just bring it on already!

427
00:29:55.770 --> 00:29:59.780
That straw hat of yours
reminds me of a certain man,

428
00:29:59.780 --> 00:30:02.820
and it really pisses me off!

429
00:30:02.820 --> 00:30:04.200
It reminds me...

430
00:30:04.910 --> 00:30:07.660
of that damn red-haired bastard!

431
00:30:08.290 --> 00:30:09.120
"Red-haired"?!

432
00:30:09.620 --> 00:30:11.120
You said "red-haired"!

433
00:30:11.120 --> 00:30:13.670
Does that mean you know Shanks?!

434
00:30:13.670 --> 00:30:16.880
Huh? Yeah, but what's it to you?

435
00:30:16.880 --> 00:30:18.210
Do you... know where he is?!

436
00:30:18.210 --> 00:30:21.090
Who can say?!
I might know where he is,

437
00:30:21.090 --> 00:30:23.470
but, then again, maybe I don't!

438
00:30:24.640 --> 00:30:25.970
That makes no sense.

439
00:30:25.970 --> 00:30:27.100
Are you an idiot?

440
00:30:27.100 --> 00:30:28.770
Look who's talking!

441
00:30:29.520 --> 00:30:34.980
I'm not nice enough to tell you
what you wanna know!

442
00:30:35.310 --> 00:30:37.610
Then I'll make you tell me!

443
00:30:39.360 --> 00:30:42.320
I'll kill you before that ever happens!

444
00:30:42.950 --> 00:30:45.660
I doubt rubber can
bounce back blades...

445
00:30:46.030 --> 00:30:47.120
Nope, it can't!

446
00:30:50.790 --> 00:30:53.210
Chop-Chop Slicecracker!

447
00:30:55.880 --> 00:31:00.630
Can't dodge in midair, can you?!

448
00:31:01.460 --> 00:31:02.800
Can too!

449
00:31:07.180 --> 00:31:10.310
Oh, my! Quite interesting!

450
00:31:10.970 --> 00:31:12.480
Same to you!

451
00:31:12.480 --> 00:31:14.690
Gum-Gum Pistol!

452
00:31:16.020 --> 00:31:17.900
Your moves are interesting,

453
00:31:17.900 --> 00:31:20.230
but they leave you wide open!

454
00:31:20.940 --> 00:31:23.070
Time to carve you up!

455
00:31:22.570 --> 00:31:23.780
Gum-Gum...

456
00:31:23.780 --> 00:31:25.660
Chop-Chop Quick Escape!

457
00:31:25.660 --> 00:31:27.490
Sickle!

458
00:31:33.750 --> 00:31:35.290
Not good enough, "Gum-Gum"!

459
00:31:40.630 --> 00:31:43.670
Damn, you keep coming apart!

460
00:31:44.010 --> 00:31:47.050
Wh-What a fight...

461
00:31:47.050 --> 00:31:48.800
It's like something out of a dream.

462
00:31:49.220 --> 00:31:51.810
Hey... Y-You see that?

463
00:31:51.810 --> 00:31:53.100
You dumbass!

464
00:31:53.100 --> 00:31:54.930
Keep pretending to be knocked out!

465
00:31:54.930 --> 00:31:59.770
Get caught up in that, and you'd
never have enough lives to survive!

466
00:31:59.770 --> 00:32:01.730
Chop-Chop Cannon!

467
00:32:04.150 --> 00:32:05.740
Separate!

468
00:32:10.200 --> 00:32:13.040
Well?! Do you see now, short stuff?!

469
00:32:21.670 --> 00:32:22.630
You bastard!

470
00:32:22.630 --> 00:32:27.090
Oh? Can't handle
a little scratch to your face?

471
00:32:27.550 --> 00:32:29.260
How dare you...?

472
00:32:29.260 --> 00:32:33.060
How dare you damage this hat?!

473
00:32:33.060 --> 00:32:34.310
Huh?

474
00:32:34.720 --> 00:32:36.520
This is my treasure!

475
00:32:36.520 --> 00:32:39.730
No one damages this hat
and gets away with it!

476
00:32:41.480 --> 00:32:45.820
Yeah. I swore to the person
who gave me this straw hat

477
00:32:45.820 --> 00:32:48.150
that I'd gather a crew
and become a pirate!

478
00:32:48.910 --> 00:32:52.030
I thought there was nothing
that could faze him...

479
00:32:53.490 --> 00:32:57.250
but he looks pretty upset.

480
00:33:00.250 --> 00:33:04.000
It would seem that hat
has a history to it.

481
00:33:04.000 --> 00:33:04.960
That's right!

482
00:33:04.960 --> 00:33:07.840
Hmm? Is it that important of a hat?

483
00:33:13.890 --> 00:33:15.640
In that case...

484
00:33:15.640 --> 00:33:16.890
take better care of it!

485
00:33:33.410 --> 00:33:35.330
I'll leave this hat with you.

486
00:33:35.990 --> 00:33:38.330
It means a lot to me.

487
00:33:38.330 --> 00:33:39.660
Take good care of it!

488
00:33:46.750 --> 00:33:50.010
Come bring it back to me someday...

489
00:33:52.090 --> 00:33:54.100
once you've become a great pirate!

490
00:33:55.510 --> 00:33:58.020
That's our promise... Luffy!

491
00:34:07.940 --> 00:34:11.490
You call this filthy
straw hat a treasure?

492
00:34:11.490 --> 00:34:13.070
Cut the crap!

493
00:34:15.320 --> 00:34:18.790
Shanks and I made
a promise on that hat!

494
00:34:18.790 --> 00:34:19.660
What?!

495
00:34:20.250 --> 00:34:23.000
You're saying this is Shanks' hat?!

496
00:34:23.750 --> 00:34:25.670
No wonder it seemed familiar!

497
00:34:26.170 --> 00:34:29.130
He always wore this around me!

498
00:34:29.130 --> 00:34:30.210
Huh?

499
00:34:30.210 --> 00:34:32.720
You and Shanks sailed
aboard the same ship?!

500
00:34:32.720 --> 00:34:36.470
Yeah, back during our
pirate apprenticeships.

501
00:34:36.470 --> 00:34:38.220
We were crewmates...

502
00:34:38.720 --> 00:34:42.140
me and that damn,
detestable, red-haired bastard!

503
00:34:43.850 --> 00:34:46.690
Shanks is a great man!

504
00:34:46.690 --> 00:34:48.360
You, his crewmate?!

505
00:34:48.360 --> 00:34:51.570
Don't compare yourself to him!

506
00:34:51.570 --> 00:34:54.530
Chop-Chop Quick Escape!

507
00:34:55.990 --> 00:34:57.530
Hi, I'm Buggy!

508
00:34:59.540 --> 00:35:03.160
Never say you and Shanks
were crewmates ever again!

509
00:35:06.500 --> 00:35:09.130
I can say whatever
I want about Shanks!

510
00:35:13.010 --> 00:35:14.090
Spill it!

511
00:35:14.090 --> 00:35:16.760
What happened between you two?!

512
00:35:17.850 --> 00:35:19.310
Damn!

513
00:35:19.310 --> 00:35:21.680
You actually ripped up my treasure!

514
00:35:24.560 --> 00:35:26.560
Wanna know that badly?

515
00:35:27.310 --> 00:35:30.020
He's the one person...

516
00:35:30.020 --> 00:35:33.070
I absolutely cannot forgive!

517
00:35:33.690 --> 00:35:37.450
I'll curse him for the rest of my life!

518
00:35:37.450 --> 00:35:41.700
I'll never forgive him!
